UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2057
1 Liske, and Catherine McFarland (Mike) Wilson; three grandchildren, Melinda Catherine
2 (Brent) Fry, Mary Catherine (Eric) Soister, and Drew Allen Liske; four great-
3 grandchildren, Mason Rawlins Fry, Lillian Grace Fry, Joseph Grant Soister, and Laurel
4 Ruth Soister; and a host of family and friends; and
5 WHEREAS, the passing of Joseph Hardin McFarland has left a void that can never
6 be filled and he will be missed greatly by his family, friends, and the community of
7 Bowling Green, Kentucky;
8 NOW, THEREFORE,
9 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
10 Kentucky:
11 Section 1. The Senate expresses its deep sense of sorrow upon the passing of
12 Joseph Hardin McFarland and extends to his family, friends, and community its sincerest
13 condolences.
14 Section 2. When the Senate adjourns this day, it does so in honor and loving
15 memory of Joseph Hardin McFarland.
16 Section 3. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
17 Resolution to Senator Mike Wilson for delivery to the family.
